metadata
data about data: format, source, purpose, quality, relationships with other data.
Please explain concept 'metadata': *what is metadata about *name >=2 examples of information it can contain
User has to correctly identify what metadata is about (data) — score 4/10. User has to correctly name at least two examples of information it can contain (format, source, purpose, quality, relationships with other data) — each correct example contributes 3/10, so 2 examples = 6/10. Perfect score math formula: 4/10 + 2 * 3/10 = 10/10.
